Cosponsored by Representative HASENFUS of Readfield and
Senators: BEEBE-CENTER of Knox, CURRY of Waldo.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 25 MRSA §1502, 6th ¶, as amended by PL 1989, c. 757, is further amended
3 to read:
4 Municipal and county jails shall at all times be available for detention of persons
5 arrested on criminal charges by any Maine state, county or any other municipal law
6 enforcement officers. In those municipalities where full-time supervision of the jail is not
7 provided by the municipality, full responsibility for the safekeeping and welfare of any
8 person detained shall rest rests solely with the arresting officer. Expense of any
9 municipality or any damage to the jail resulting from the use of its jail by any arresting
10 officer shall must be reimbursed to the municipality by the law enforcement agency for
11 which the arresting officer is acting.
12 SUMMARY
1133 Current law requires municipal and county jails to be available at all times for detention
1144 of persons arrested by state or any other law enforcement officers. This bill requires
1155 municipal and county jails to be available at all times for detention of persons arrested on
1166 criminal charges by Maine state, county or municipal law enforcement officers.
